---
export const prerender = true;

import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const structuredData = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "AboutPage",
  "name": "About PaperLanterns.ink",
  "description": "Preserving the intimate conversations that shaped our world. A curated collection of historical letters from public domain archives.",
  "url": "https://collections.paperlanterns.ink/about",
  "mainEntity": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "PaperLanterns.ink",
    "url": "https://paperlanterns.ink",
    "description": "Cataloging Indian public domain works and historical correspondence",
    "founder": {
      "@type": "Person",
      "name": "Bhuvan Mehra"
    }
  }
};
---

<Base
  title="About - PaperLanterns.ink"
  description="Preserving the intimate conversations that shaped our world. A curated collection of historical letters from public domain archives."
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(structuredData)} />
  <!-- Hero -->
  <div class="about-hero">
    <div class="hero-label">About the Project</div>
    <h1 class="hero-title">Preserving the intimate<br>conversations that shaped<br>our world</h1>
    <p class="hero-subtitle">
      Before the age of instant communication, every written word carried weight.
      Letters were deliberate, speeches carefully crafted, and each sentence intentionally chosen.
      These documents reveal the human experiences—hopes, fears, loves, and dreams of those who came before us.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Vision Section -->
  <div class="content-section">
    <div class="section-label">My Vision</div>
    <div class="section-content">
      <h2 class="section-title">Why Letters Matter</h2>
      <p class="section-text">
        Letters offer an intimate window into the minds of great thinkers, writers, and historical
        figures. Unlike their published works, letters reveal the personal thoughts, daily struggles,
        and human connections that shaped history.
      </p>
      <p class="section-text">
        These historical letters, speeches, and essays are frozen moments that can awaken human capabilities.
        Many documents remain neglected, waiting for rediscovery. I treat these materials as works of art,
        windows into the soul, and bridges across time.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Behind the Page Section -->
  <div class="content-section">
    <div class="section-label">Behind the Page</div>
    <div class="section-content">
      <h2 class="section-title">A Labor of Love</h2>
      <p class="section-text">
        I'm Bhuvan, and I'm pursuing a larger initiative cataloging Indian public domain works.
        On the <a href="https://paperlanterns.ink" target="_blank" rel="noopener">main Paper Lanterns site</a>,
        I curate individual letters and documents with rich historical context.
      </p>
      <p class="section-text">
        This collections site serves a different purpose: I clean up historic letter collections in their entirety,
        fixing OCR errors and doing manual quality checks to preserve complete correspondences. This work is done
        almost entirely manually, one letter at a time, using AI tools to assist with formatting and verification
        but without specialized technical infrastructure.
      </p>
      <p class="section-text">
        This is truly a labor of love. If you're an expert in OCR techniques or historical document preservation
        and would like to help improve this process, I'd be grateful for your guidance. You can reach me on
        <a href="https://twitter.com/bhuvan_mehra" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Twitter</a> or
        <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/bhuvaneshmehra" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>.
      </p>
      <p class="section-text">
        Inspired by <em>Letters of Note</em> by Shaun Usher, I'm collecting documents carefully verified
        for authenticity and historical accuracy. I believe these materials contain timeless wisdom and beauty
        that should be accessible to everyone.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Part of Dhwani Section -->
  <div class="content-section">
    <div class="section-label">The Bigger Picture</div>
    <div class="section-content">
      <h2 class="section-title">Part of Dhwani.ink</h2>
      <p class="section-text">
        This project is part of my larger work with <a href="https://dhwani.ink" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Dhwani.ink</a>,
        where I'm building a curated directory of Indian literary and historical works in the public domain.
        Dhwani—a Kannada word meaning "voice" or "sound"—represents these works as voices from history, echoing across time.
      </p>
      <p class="section-text">
        While Dhwani aggregates links to thousands of public domain works from repositories like Archive.org,
        Project Gutenberg, and Wikisource, PaperLanterns focuses on the intimate art of correspondence.
        Together, they address what I see as a profound cultural apathy toward preserving our literary heritage.
      </p>
      <p class="section-text">
        As I wrote on Dhwani: "This is our history. And if we don't preserve our past, the future will be
        nothing but a shitty remake of it." These letter collections are one way I'm working to ensure
        these voices—these windows into the minds of great thinkers—remain accessible to future generations.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Sources Section -->
  <div class="content-section">
    <div class="section-label">Sources</div>
    <div class="section-content">
      <h2 class="section-title">Where I Find Collections</h2>
      <p class="section-text">
        My primary sources include Archive.org, Wikisource, Project Gutenberg, and university
        special collections. I carefully verify that all materials are free from copyright
        restrictions before publication.
      </p>
      <p class="section-text">
        Each collection includes source citations linking back to the original archive,
        ensuring transparency and enabling further research.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  /* ==================== HERO ==================== */
  .about-hero {
    grid-column: 1 / -1;
    padding: var(--space-9xl) 0 var(--space-8xl) 0;
    text-align: center;
    animation: slideUp 0.8s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
  }

  .hero-label {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--text-label);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-widest);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-label);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .hero-title {
    font-size: var(--text-hero);
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: var(--leading-tight);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-tight);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5xl);
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }

  .hero-subtitle {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 20px;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-weight: 400;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    line-height: var(--leading-loose);
  }

  /* ==================== CONTENT SECTIONS ==================== */
  .content-section {
    grid-column: 1 / -1;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(12, 1fr);
    gap: var(--grid-gap);
    padding: var(--space-8xl) 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .section-label {
    grid-column: 1 / 4;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--text-label);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-widest);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-label);
    font-weight: 700;
    position: sticky;
    top: 160px;
    align-self: start;
  }

  .section-content {
    grid-column: 5 / 12;
  }

  .section-title {
    font-size: 48px;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -1px;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3xl);
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }

  .section-text {
    font-size: 20px;
    line-height: var(--leading-loose);
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3xl);
  }

  .section-text:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* ==================== PROCESS STEPS ==================== */
  .process-steps {
    margin-top: var(--space-6xl);
  }

  .process-step {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 80px 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-3xl);
    margin-bottom: 56px;
  }

  .process-step:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .step-number {
    font-size: 56px;
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--color-border);
    letter-spacing: -2px;
  }

  .step-content h3 {
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-title);
  }

  .step-content p {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  /* ==================== PRINCIPLES ==================== */
  .principles-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-5xl);
    margin-top: var(--space-6xl);
  }

  .principle-card {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg,
      rgba(250, 250, 249, 0.8) 0%,
      rgba(247, 246, 243, 0.9) 100%);
    padding: var(--space-4xl);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent-end);
    transition: all var(--transition-base);
  }

  .principle-card:hover {
    transform: translateX(4px);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.03);
  }

  .principle-card h3 {
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    color: var(--color-accent-start);
    letter-spacing: -0.3px;
  }

  .principle-card p {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--text-small);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  /* ==================== RESPONSIVE ==================== */
  @media (max-width: 1100px) {
    .hero-title {
      font-size: 64px;
    }

    .section-label {
      grid-column: 1 / 5;
    }

    .section-content {
      grid-column: 5 / 13;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about-hero {
      padding: var(--space-7xl) 0 var(--space-6xl) 0;
    }

    .hero-title {
      font-size: 48px;
    }

    .hero-subtitle {
      font-size: var(--text-subtitle);
    }

    .section-label,
    .section-content {
      grid-column: 1 / -1;
    }

    .section-label {
      position: relative;
      top: 0;
      margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
    }

    .section-title {
      font-size: 36px;
    }

    .section-text {
      font-size: var(--text-subtitle);
    }

    .process-step {
      grid-template-columns: 60px 1fr;
      gap: var(--space-lg);
      margin-bottom: var(--space-4xl);
    }

    .step-number {
      font-size: 40px;
    }

    .principles-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: var(--space-3xl);
    }
  }
</style>
